    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style and culture named for the site at Grotta Romanelli, Calabria, Italy, which dates to around 8,000 before present. It is particularly characterized by cave art consisting of stylized and geometric incised patterns.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo y cultura que lleva el nombre del sitio en Grotta Romanelli, Calabria, Italia fechado alrededor del 8,000 antes del presente. Se caracteriza particularmente por arte rupestre que consiste en modelos estilizados y geométricos incisos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de stijl en cultuur genoemd naar de archeologische vindplaats bij Grotta Romanelli in het Italiaanse Calabrië, die stamt uit circa 6000 v. Chr. Deze kenmerkt zich door grotschilderingen die bestaan uit gestileerde en geometrische ingekerfde patronen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指稱以義大利卡拉比利亞（Calabria）的果塔羅曼尼利（Grotta Romanelli）遺址命名的中石器時代風格與文化，可追溯至考古紀元元的前八千年左右。此文化特別以風格化的幾何雕刻圖案所構成的洞穴藝術著稱。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
